Third-party pattern sources
----------------------------
The v1 detector patterns are clean-room re-derivations from publicly documented
credential formats (vendor prefixes such as AKIA, ghp_, sk-ant-, AIza; PEM armor;
RFC1918 ranges; RFC-style email/URI shapes). No detector regex was copied from a
third-party project, so no third-party license attribution is required for v1.

Precision techniques (per-charset entropy thresholds, noise/placeholder
rejection, Base32 structural gating, exact vendor token shapes) were informed by
the following permissively-licensed projects and official vendor documentation,
and re-implemented clean-room (no code copied):
  - gitleaks — MIT (verified): keyword/stopword-style filtering concept.
  - detect-secrets (Yelp) — Apache-2.0 (verified): per-charset entropy thresholds
    and sequential/UUID/repeat noise rejection.
  - GitHub Docs / AWS IAM Docs — official format specifications (facts).
TruffleHog (AGPL-3.0) was deliberately NOT used: its source was not consulted for
reuse. The offline AWS Base32 structural check was derived from independent public
security research, not from any AGPL source.

